### Feature Description

## 1. Feature Request

I’d like to request that the **Guides** page (`/guides`) support filtering by category through a query parameter.
For example:

* `https://roadmap.sh/guides?category=textual`
* `https://roadmap.sh/guides?category=question`

When a `category` query parameter is provided, only those guides matching the category should be shown.
If no parameter is given, all guides are shown (current behavior).

This will help users bookmark or share category‑filtered views and improve discoverability.


<img width="948" height="526" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/056a542e-a167-4397-b850-909f77a5edac" />

---

## 2. Relevant Code Files / Locations

Below are candidate files or folders in the repo that are likely relevant and should be updated. (You may need to adjust paths depending on actual file structure.)

* `src/pages/guides.astro` (or similar route file for `/guides`)
* `src/components/GuideList.astro` or `src/components/Guides/GuideList.astro`
* `src/components/GuideCard.astro`
* `src/data/guides/*.md` (or wherever guide metadata / frontmatter is stored)
* `src/lib/guides.ts` (or `queries/guides.ts`) — utility or data loading logic

These are examples you can inspect in the repo structure and adapt.

---

## 3. Example Implementation Snippet

Here’s an illustrative sketch (Astro / JavaScript) of how you might implement query filtering client‑side or at render time:

```ts
---
// In `src/pages/guides.astro`
import { getAllGuides } from '../lib/guides';

const allGuides = await getAllGuides();  
const url = new URL(Astro.request.url);
const categoryParam = url.searchParams.get('category');

// filter guides if categoryParam is provided
const filteredGuides = categoryParam
  ? allGuides.filter(g => g.category.toLowerCase() === categoryParam.toLowerCase())
  : allGuides;
---

<GuideList guides={filteredGuides} />

<script is:inline type="module">
  // if you want client-side sync of URL → UI
  const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
  const current = params.get('category');
  window.history.replaceState({}, '', window.location.pathname + (current ? `?category=${current}` : ''));
</script>
```

And for the `getAllGuides` helper:

```ts
// src/lib/guides.ts
import guideFiles from '../data/guides/*.md';  // or whichever loader is used

export interface Guide {
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  category: string;  // “Textual”, “Question”, etc.
  // other metadata
}

export async function getAllGuides(): Promise<Guide[]> {
  const guides = await Promise.all(
    Object.entries(guideFiles).map(async ([_, file]) => {
      const { frontmatter } = await file.metadata();
      return {
        title: frontmatter.title,
        slug: file.slug,
        category: frontmatter.category || 'textual',  // default if missing
        // …
      }
    })
  );
  return guides;
}
```

Optionally, you could also do filtering server-side or at build time, but a client‑aware version is a good start.

---

## 4. Tests / Test Cases

You may write tests (e.g. for a utility function) or manual QA scenarios like:

* **No `category` param** → all guides displayed
* `?category=textual` → only guides with category `"textual"` (case-insensitive)
* `?category=question` → only guides with category `"question"`
* Invalid/unrecognized `category` value → fallback to “none found” or show all (depending on desired logic)
* Changing the query param in the browser should update the visible list
* Bookmarking a category URL should render correctly when visited directly

If the repo uses a testing framework (e.g. Vitest / Jest), you can add unit tests around the filtering helper function.

---

## 5. Thank You 🙏

Thanks for maintaining this awesome project — `developer-roadmap` and roadmap.sh are super helpful to the community.
I’m happy to contribute a PR for this feature once the design is agreed upon.

